Hi guys! I have a few questions regarding ladies learning programming:
1) Does the UK government or some organizations provide grants or scholarships for ladies who want to learn programming?
2) are there any schools/companies focused on teaching back-end development?
3) what are the most valued programming development programs in London (e.g schools, private companies) based on demand/hiring success rate?
4) Do you know any private mentors who are focused on back-end development? What are their fees?
Thank you!!!

Hello all!! Anyone have any thoughts about getting past the beginner phase? I've gone through several training courses CodeAcademy, Treehouse, YouTube, Udacity, Udemy. Every time I feel like I'm taking a few steps back by starting over but I'm also learning something new from each course.  (eg. It wasn't until my third course that I really understood that a method call like setText() was a method like any other but defined elsewhere.) (eg2. Didn't understand for the longest time what @Override meant!)  So now I'm wanting to make my own app instead of just following along and I'm really stuck at this is what I want to accomplish, but I'm not sure what Views, API's, etc are the best to get me there.
